&lt;h2&gt;Durga Puja 2025: A Kaleidoscope of Creativity in Kolkata&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="durga-puja-2025-a-kaleidoscope-of-creativity-in-kolkata"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#durga-puja-2025-a-kaleidoscope-of-creativity-in-kolkata" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Introduction&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="introduction"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#introduction" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Veena and I found ourselves in India during Durga Pooja, a perfect opportunity to revisit Kolkata, a city close to my heart. I was excited to witness every street transformed into an open gallery, a blend of creativity and tradition. This post is a visual journey, so I&amp;rsquo;ll let my pictures tell the story!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Start&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="start"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#start" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kolkata is in West Bengal, and whenever I think about West Bengal, the first thing that flashes in my head is:
&lt;img src="https://i.postimg.cc/8CNw8d71/PXL-20250930-170537992.jpg" alt="Kolkata Tea" loading="lazy" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After a hiatus of almost forty years, I was thrilled to return to Kolkata. And the first thing on my agenda? To relish their tea in a traditional clay cup, a taste of nostalgia and a journey of rediscovery!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now that we&amp;rsquo;ve covered that, let&amp;rsquo;s begin exploring the pandals I visited. I&amp;rsquo;ve mentioned the word &amp;lsquo;pandal&amp;rsquo; several times—what does it mean? A pandal is a &lt;strong&gt;temporary structure&lt;/strong&gt; used for festivals, religious ceremonies, or social events. It is a temporary structure, usually in place for about a month. &lt;strong&gt;All structures and deities you see below don&amp;rsquo;t exist when you read this.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
